alarm.sh

About
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
	Small shell script to inform you of events at certain times.

Install
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
	Just 'cp alarm.sh /usr/local/bin'

Usage
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

	alarm.sh can run in two modes. The first is the daemon mode in which it
	will notify you of events when they occur and the other is the edit 
	mode through which you can add, change, delete and list events. alarm.sh
	in daemon mode should be run under X.

	Daemon mode (actually receiving notifications)
	----------------------------------------------
	$ DISPLAY=localhost:0
	$ export DISPLAY
	$ ./alarm.sh --daemon&
	
	Adding alarms
	-------------
	$ alarm.sh -n -t "20:15" -m "Meet and greet with John in 15 minutes" 
	$ alarm.sh -n -r -t "friday" -m "Friday beer-drinking competition tonight"

	Changing alarm
	--------------
	$ alarm.sh -c -i2 -t "thursday" -m "Thursday beer-drinking competition tonight"

	Deleting alarm
	--------------
	$ alarm.sh -d -i2

	Listing set alarms
	------------------
	$ dev/alarm/alarm.sh -l

	 id | m |                 date | message
	----+---+----------------------+---------------------------------------------
	  1 |   |     2005-04-11 20:00 | Rick bellen
	  2 |   |     2005-04-16 00:00 | Wouter verjaardag stairway vanavond
	  3 |   |     2005-04-26 00:00 | Hardrock feest morgen

	id      = Notification ID (use with -i).
	m       = Mode ('n'ormal, 'r'ecurring).
	date    = The absolute ('2005-04-11 20:00') or relative ('friday') date & 
	          time of the event.
	message = The message to show when the event is triggered.
	

